==Tagalog==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|tl|mey|me||nonstandard}}
* {{alt|tl|mi||obsolete}}

===Etymology===
From Proto-Central Philippine ''*may'' (existential marker). See also {{ncog|poz-pro|*mai||and}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{tl-pr|+,me<q:colloquial>|mey<a:dialectal,Batangas>|syll=+}}

===Particle===
{{tl-head|particle|b=+}}

# {{n-g|particle used as an existential marker}}: to [[be]]; to [[have]]
#: {{syn|tl|mayroon|meron}}
#: {{ant|tl|wala}}
#: {{ux|tl|'''May''' tubig sa bahay.|'''There is''' water in the house.}}
#: {{ux|tl|'''May''' pagkain ako rito, sa'yo na lang.|I '''have''' food here, have it.}}

====Usage notes====
* '''May''' is used immediately before the thing possessed or existing, whereas {{m|tl|mayroon}} can be separated by [[enclitic]]s (e.g. {{m|tl|lang}}, {{m|tl|kaya}}, and {{m|tl|ako}}). Sentences like *''may ako pagkain'' would be ungrammatical.

====Derived terms====
{{col3|tl|mema}}

====See also====
* {{l|tl|may-}}

===Preposition===
{{tl-prep|b=+}}

# {{ng|used after {{m|tl|sa}}}}: [[by]]; [[around]]; [[near]]
#: {{ux|tl|Kunin mo ang araro doon '''sa may''' puno ng mangga.|Get the shovel '''by''' the mango tree.|lit=Get the shovel at the place '''with''' the mango tree.}}

===Further reading===
* {{R:Pambansang Diksiyonaryo}}

